{
  "text": "6. q-ary Robust Positioning Sequences. In this section, we modify the construction of Berkowitz and Kopparty and give a new class of q-ary positioning sequences robust to a constant fraction of errors. We first review Berkowitz and Kopparty's work. Theorem 6.1 (Berkowitz and Kopparty [CITATION_1] ). Fix a generator g of F * q . Let G = (\u03c3 \u03c3 \u03c3 0 , \u03c3 \u03c3 \u03c3 1 , . . . , \u03c3 \u03c3 \u03c3 q k \u22121 ) be a (k, q)-Gray code. For each \u03c3 \u03c3 \u03c3 i , let f i (x) \u2208 F q [x] be the unique interpolating polynomial of degree k + 1 so that",
  "citation_candidates": [
